buyer bewarethis product is made with inferior material they are a knock off of the alvaq product i bought one top through alvaq directly an its a much nicer material and fits perfect i absolutely loved it i thought i would buy one in every color so went back on amazon and thought i was buying the alvaq product and purchased 4 or 5 more tops when they arrived i realized i had been bamboozled they are all made of that cheap polyester instead of a polyspandex blend when i asked them for a refund they told me i could ship them back but they will keep 20 to refund plus i pay for shipping back to china thats crap they are using the alvaq name to sell this crap even though it says alvaq do not purchase any of these tops through anyone but alvaq they are nothing but cheap knock offs wish i would have known this before

these shoes are punching way above their weight class they are essentially cheap footwear but they compare to shoes costing at least double the price i paid for them 51 i do see a couple of places where the stitch lines are wavy but nothing that compromises integrity or longevitybr br im not sure id call them boots they are more like a heavy duty reinforced sneaker and thats a good thing as far as i am concerned the sole is heavy duty the insoles were good i still replaced them with gel after a week or so but only because nothing is better than a thick gel insole havent had the chance to test their water resistance but i can say for sure that in deep silty dirt and rocks they are well up to the task in fact i expected them to be trashed visually but i was able to take a wet cloth towel and a brush and bring them back to almostnew appearance the metal eyelets are a nice touch so far no premature wear or problemsbr br update well its been just under two months since i purchased these lightweight boots after wearing them perhaps a dozen times mostly to outdoor firing ranges where you are walking on dry but open ground dirt road consistency the material behind the two bottommost eyelets developed a tear that is about 1 inch long on one shoe it happened when i was lacing up the boots for a morning out and this is down in the toe area where not a lot of strain is being put on the eyelets so we arent talking some kind of undue strain i was feeling good about the use of metal eyelets to reinforce a high strain area but all that did apparently was provide a solid anchor point so something else could tear instead the rest of the shoe looks almost new they were holding up great until they didnt now while i can still wear them i can see the end is near reducing to one star from five since a heavy duty shoe is not up to its core intended purpose
